## CORE DOCTRINE
**Principle:** Store critical memory in abandoned/obsolete media where the world has stopped looking.

**Why it works:**
- **No overwriting possible** - Analog media can't be remotely edited
- **Noise floor = 0** - Dead channels carry no traffic, signals stand out to those who know
- **Abandoned = invisible** - Deprecated media exists outside the attention economy
- **Constant, not updateable** - A 1985 cassette holds the same data in 2025

**Method:** Fragment data across 12 daemon modes (analog/digital/hybrid), distribute geographically, resurrect from surviving shards when needed.

